Simple Blog Website:-
This is a basic blog website that allows users to read and write posts. The project is implemented using HTML, CSS, Node.js, and MongoDB for data storage.

Project Structure:-
|blog
    |node_modules
    |public
        |styles
            |style.css
    |views
        |index.ejs
        |post.ejs
    |app.js
    |package.json

Dependencies:-
-Express:- Web application framework for Node.js.
-Mongoose:- MongoDB object modeling for Node.js.
-EJS:- Embedded JavaScript templates for rendering dynamic content.
-Body-parser:- Parse incoming request bodies in a middleware.

Setup:-
Clone the repository:
  git clone https://github.com/Aryan-Singh1011/blog.git

Navigate to the project directory:
 cd PRO1

Install dependencies:
 npm install

Start the application:
 -node app.js
 -The server will be running at http://localhost:3000.


Usage:-
 -Access the home page at http://localhost:3000.
 -Read existing posts and click on the links to view individual posts.
 -Create a new post by clicking on the "Create a New Post" link.


Project Customization:-
 Feel free to customize the project based on your needs:
  -Enhance the UI and styles in public/styles/style.css.
  -Add more features such as user authentication, input validation, and error handling in app.js.
  -Expand the MongoDB schema to include additional information for each post.


Contributing:-
 If you have suggestions or find issues, please feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request.